    "narrative_summary": "The BRCA2 c.1141G>A (p.Asp381Asn) missense change is listed in several variant databases but has not been linked to a specific disease phenotype in the extracted literature. It appears in a supplementary table of a large\u2011scale multifactorial likelihood analysis of BRCA1/2 variants and is also recorded in a Chinese cohort study and a mycosis fungoides genomic analysis, without any explicit pathogenic interpretation.\nClinical evidence from the ENIGMA\u2011based multifactorial likelihood study assigns the variant a likely\u2011benign classification, noting conflicting interpretations but ultimately supporting benignity (combined likelihood ratio not exceeding the threshold for pathogenicity) [PMC6772163]. The other two reports merely catalogue the variant among many others and provide no interpretive comment [PMC6617753][PMC6282857].\nOverall, the available data do not support a pathogenic role for BRCA2 c.1141G>A. The most robust assessment, derived from a quantitative multifactorial analysis, favors a likely\u2011benign status, and no functional or population\u2011frequency evidence contradicts this interpretation.",
    "structured_summary": {
        "overall_pathogenicity": "benign",
        "pathogenicity_counts": {
            "supports pathogenicity": 0,
            "uncertain": 0,
            "supports benignity": 1
        },
        "conflicting_evidence": false
    },
